-- BNDES Furnishes $16.1 Million for Brazilian Sanitation Projects
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2013-07-01T17:19:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-01/bndes-furnishes-16-1-million-for-brazilian-sanitation-projects.html
Banco Nacional de Desenvolvimento
Economico e Social,  Brazil ’s development bank, will loan two
units of CAB Ambiental 35.7 million reais ($16.1 million) for
sanitation projects in Sao Paulo state.  Aguas de Andradina will receive 27 million reais and use
part of the funds to expand sewage collection and treatment
infrastructure in the city of Andradina, the Rio de Janeiro-based lender said today on its  website . The company expects to
treat all of the city’s sewage by 2015, up from 8 percent last
year.  Aguas de Castilho will use the remainder to extend sewage
collection and treatment services to the entire city of Castilho
by 2015, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
